Dockerfile Instructions: ????

FROM ---- Defines the base image for the Docker image. Must be the first instruction.   FROM ubuntu:22.04
RUN  ---- Executes commands during image build and creates a new image layer.           RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y nginx
COPY ---  Copies files/directories from the host to the image.                          COPY app.jar /app/
ADD  ---  Similar to COPY, but can extract local tar files and download URLs.           ADD app.tar.gz /app/
WORKDIR --- Sets the working directory for subsequent instructions                      WORKDIR /app
ENV     --- Sets environment variables inside the container.                            ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-17
EXPOSE  --- Documents the port the container listens on.                                EXPOSE 8080
CMD    --- Specifies the default command/arguments when the container starts.           CMD ["java","-jar","app.jar"]
ENTRYPOINT --- Defines the main executable that always runs.                            ENTRYPOINT ["java","-jar"]
ARG --- Defines build-time variables available during image build only.                 ARG VERSION=1.0
USER --- Specifies the user to run the container as.                                    USER appuser
LABEL---- Adds metadata to the image.                                                   LABEL maintainer="devops@example.com"

Container is running but application is not accessible. What will you do?
Answer:
First I will debug step by step:
Check container status:
docker ps
Check logs:
docker logs <container_id>
Check port mapping:
docker port <container_id>
Verify application is listening inside container:
docker exec -it <container_id> sh
netstat -tulnp
Common issue: app running on wrong port or not exposed using -p.


Container exits immediately after starting. Why?
Answer:

Common reasons:
Main process finished
Missing foreground process
Wrong CMD/ENTRYPOINT

Check logs:
docker logs <container>

Fix:
Ensure long-running process (e.g. nginx, java app)
Use:
CMD ["nginx", "-g", "daemon off;"]

